      • readLogFile

        public void readLogFile(String fileName,
                        String protocol,
                        String index,
                        String type)
                 throws IOException
        Process a log path on local file system which contains the relevant parameters as below.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the String path to the log directory on file system
        protocol - whether to process 'http' or 'FTP'
        index - the index name to write logs to
        type - one of the available protocols from which Mudrod logs are obtained.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is an error reading anything from the fileName provided.
